The Nigeria Army on Thursday inaugurated a General Court Martial to prosecute 70 personnel for defaulting in the counter-insurgency operation in the North East. <img class="alignnone  wp-image-1259439" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="Army, insurgency" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/maxresdefault-1.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Acting General Officer Commanding (GOC) 7 Division, Brig.-Gen. Abdul Khalifa said the court was inaugurated in accordance with Section 131(2) (d) of the Armed Forces Act, CAP A20 LFN 2004. Khalifa said the court would exercise its duties within the confines of the law and military regimentation principles. He added that principles of justice, equity and fairness would guide the proceeding of the court. Khalifa said the aim was to encourage compliance with ethical standards and promote discipline to ensure the successful implementation of military operations. “Acts of cowardice, desertion, un-soldierly and other forms of indiscipline has no place in any army executing war,” he said. The commander, however, enjoined the court members to be fair in discharging their duties. (NAN)  Vanguard Chief of Army Staff, Lt.-Gen. Tukur Buratai, has warned that any officer or soldier whose indecisive act will lead to killing of personnel in an operation would be sanctioned. October 23, 2018 In "News" ABUJA— Chief of Army Staff, Lt. General Tukur Buratai, has ordered the military trial of two Major Generals of the Nigerian Army for what military sources said were offences contrary to service discipline. May 6, 2016 In "News" The General Officer Commanding, 2 Division, Nigerian Army,  Maj-Gen. Okwudili Azinta, has inaugurated a General Court Martial (GCM) to try erring personnel in the division. December 17, 2018 In "News"